To compile:
> gcc client1.c -o client1
> gcc server1.c -o server1

To run and test:
> ./server1 & (to run server in background)
> ./client1 <operation> <numbers to operate>

The supported operations are addition (+ character), substraction (- character) and multiplication (x character)
The numbers to operate have a limit of ten.

Example:
> ./client1 + 1 2 3 4 5
